Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Dilute the @chicken stock{1%sachet} in 500ml boiling @water{500%ml}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Quarter the @mushrooms{125%g}.

Place a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} over medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

When the oil is hot, add the onion, mushrooms and @chorizo{100%g}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan use a normal one and transfer the risotto to an ovenproof dish before placing it in the oven.

Add the @risotto rice{225%g}, @salt{1/2%tsp} and half the @Italian herbs{1/2%sachet} to the pan.

Cook, stirring, until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the warm stock and stir well to combine.

Bring back up to the boil then pop a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}).

Bake in the oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{30-35%minutes}.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in a knob of @?butter{} if you have any.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Roughly tear half the @basil{5%g}(roughly torn) leaves.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if needed.

Divide risotto between plates.

Roughly tear the @mozzarella{125%g}(roughly torn) and garnish your dish.

Sprinkle over torn basil leaves and cracked pepper.

Drizzle the @balsamic glaze{2%sachets} over the top.